<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-357-858  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 357 858.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Byte  June 1989 v14 n6 p209(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Claris CAD: Claris's first CAD program is more than just anotherMacDraw. (Software Review) (evaluation)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Tuten, Paul.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Claris CAD is a two-dimensional drafting program for the Mac,based on MacDraw II.andP;  The package retails for $799, with upgradesfor MacDraw II owners available for $399.andP;  Claris CAD is more thana new release of MacDraw II.andP;  It is powerful and versatile enoughto compete with VersaCAD for the Mac market.andP;  The package includesdetailed documentation and a videotape to introduce Claris CADtools and concepts.andP;  Hardware requirements include one megabyte ofhard disk memory, more if you use a large-screen monitor orMultiFinder.andP;  The edit menu includes most of the usual options,along with Polar and Liner duplicate.andP;  Trim and Smooth are twomore useful features.andP;  Claris CAD runs more rapidly on the Mac SEthan VersaCAD, making it a viable alternative.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Claris Corp. (evaluation).andO;Product:   Apple Macintosh (Microcomputer) (computer programs)ClarisCAD (Computer graphics software).andO;Topic:     Computer-aided designEvaluationSoftware packages.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>